subjects.name: Systems Engineering Handbook 5th Edition
subjects.description: Core concepts and principles of Systems Engineering.

chapters.name: Systems Engineering Introduction
chapters.description: Foundational concepts, definitions, and principles of Systems Engineering.

chapters.name: System Life Cycle Concepts, Models, and Processes
chapters.description: Overview of life cycle terms, models, and processes used in SE.

chapters.name: Life Cycle Analyses and Methods
chapters.description: Covers quality characteristics, analyses, and methods that apply throughout the system life cycle.

chapters.name: Tailoring and Application Considerations
chapters.description: Guidance on tailoring SE processes and applying them across different domains and system types.
topics: Application of Systems Engineering for Specific Product Sectors

chapters.name: Systems Engineering in Practice
chapters.description: Explores practical aspects including competencies, inter-disciplinary relationships, and emerging trends.

chapters.name: Case Studies
chapters.description: Real-world case studies that illustrate the application of SE principles.

subjects.name: ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288
subjects.description: Systems and software engineering  System life cycle processes and standards.

chapters.name: Scope
chapters.description: Defines the scope and applicability of the standard.

chapters.name: Normative References
chapters.description: Lists the normative references that are indispensable for the application of the standard.

chapters.name: Terms and Definitions
chapters.description: Provides definitions for key terms used throughout the standard.

chapters.name: General Principles
chapters.description: Outlines the overarching principles and concepts that underpin the system life cycle processes.

chapters.name: Life Cycle Processes
chapters.description: Describes the set of processes that cover the entire system life cycle, grouped into four process categories.

chapters.name: Life Cycle Model Considerations
chapters.description: Discusses various life cycle model approaches and their suitability for different system development scenarios.

chapters.name: Annexes
chapters.description: Supplementary material including examples, guidance, and additional information.
